reviews.text: Delicious Italian food. Reservation preferred. Google maps reservation service did not work. I called restaurant 30 min before opening. They picked up and my table was ready for me for dinner. The place looks nice. It is a bit on the pricey side but for that location that might be fine. Bring your own vine! Parking available.

If you haven't been to this location, you are truly missing out! Fellini Newtown Square (formerly called Fellini Cafe) is my all-time favorite Italian restaurant! They're a family-owned business that takes great pride in their food and providing exceptional service.

I've been dining here for 20 years, but unfortunately, I moved to NC in 2013, so the opportunities to get back have grown few and far between. My brother and I were in the area last December, and they had just completed a renovation of the entire place‚Äîso cool to see after it being so long since we visited. The food was exactly as we remembered: fresh, delicious, and high quality!

The dressing on their salad is something I've tried to duplicate at home, but it just never hits the mark‚Äîso, I'm convinced they're using magic. :-) Fresh bread? It's like NOTHING in NC‚Äîunfortunately for me, I'm not kidding.

Anyway, they offer a very robust menu with many Italian classics and their own specialties. They've never turned down modifications on dishes‚Äîliterally, I've never had anything bad here. My mom ordered eggplant parm one time, and I don't even like eggplant‚Äîbut I liked this one. Calamari, salad, soup, pastas, pizza, desserts... they have something for everyone.

Almost forgot‚Äîthey're also BYOB, so bring your favorite bottle for everyone in your party and enjoy! The venue is small and may have slightly more seating capacity after their renovation, but we almost always made reservations before moving‚Äîwhether it be lunch or dinner. They also accept large party reservations with advance notice.

Their parking is very limited, with more signs than ever dictating "customer parking only" for various businesses. If you‚Äôre going during peak hours, be prepared to wait for a spot in the front lot. You can also buy alcohol past the bank and Verizon store at Newtown Suds (to stash in your trunk) and then walk down, or park across the (small) highway in the ACME shopping center for free.

In summation‚Ä¶ just gather your favorite people, bring some wine, and enjoy this spot!

My family and I ate here on Christmas Eve and really enjoyed it! I‚Äôd definitely recommend making a reservation to guarantee seating. It was super busy, but the food was still delicious! The sleek interior that they recently remodeled looks great. The ONLY downside (which is of nobody‚Äôs fault) is that there is very limited space inside. It didn‚Äôt bother us, but if you‚Äôre someone who needs a lot of space, just keep that in mind!

I recently had the pleasure having lunch at Fellini Cafe in Newtown Square and it was truly a memorable experience. The Grilled Artichokes were a standout dish, with the Roman artichokes perfectly grilled and paired with fresh mozzarella, green olives, sliced prosciutto, shredded parmesan, and a drizzle of truffle oil. Each bite was bursting with flavor and the combination of ingredients was simply divine.

The Fried Calamari was also a hit, with the fresh squid lightly battered and fried to perfection. The marinara sauce served alongside added a nice tangy kick to the dish.

For the main course, I tried the Involtini Fellini, a unique dish featuring veal, spinach, blue cheese, and cream. The flavors worked harmoniously together and the veal was incredibly tender.

Lastly, the Penne alla Vodka with shrimp was a comforting and indulgent choice. The tomato cream sauce reduced in vodka added a rich and creamy element to the dish, and the shrimp were cooked to perfection.

Overall, my dining experience at Fellini Cafe was exceptional. The ambiance was cozy and inviting, the service by Patricio was top-notch, and the food was absolutely delicious. I would highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a fantastic Italian dining experience in Newtown Square.
Love the food and Patrizio and Dana. Always try to be there on a Wednesday or Thursday. I always get gift cards for holidays and birthdays

detailedReviews.author: Charles Valenza
detailedReviews.text: My parents and I visited this establishment for dinner on 3/1/25, I had a reservation. First off we were warmly welcomed by a very lovely gentleman who was the manager, he brought us to our table. Its BYOB, I brought one of the wines from my private collection, it paired well with our meal overall. We started off with crispy calamari fritti, prepared to perfection, tender and absolutely delicious with marinara and the bread with EVOO, was lovely.  Now to our meals. Both my parents opted for veal parmesan, they enjoyed it. I opted for the chicken parmesan, now I have a minor critique, as a Culinarian/Foodie and a Sicilian, I am not a fan of my chicken parmesan completely drowning in sauce, I like to be able to taste the crispiness of the chicken cutlets, just lightly sauced on top & cheese. Other than that everything was great! We ended our dinner with Cannolis, they were a perfect ending. Fellini Cafe is Highly Recommended! Tell them Charlie sent ya!

When we weren‚Äôt ready to order she rolled her eyes while walking away. Got the food cold and never came to check on us. Had to ask another waitress to open our wine as our waitress never came back to check on us. Couldn‚Äôt even get a dessert because the next time she came back she just put the check on the table without asking us if there was anything else we needed, no how was the food, nothing. I‚Äôm a server too and she was a disgrace. When we got the check they add on a service charge if you use a credit card but was added on the total of the bill. When we asked for our waitress to come back we asked her about it and she rudely replied ‚Äúuse cash and you want have that problem‚Äù as she walked away. We couldn‚Äôt believe that answer she gave us. I don‚Äôt understand why they even charge a service charge is ridiculous. How cheap do you have to be to charge your customer service charge when they make all this money.
Needless to say we will NOT be back and have spread the word and will continue to do so. I have been told similar bad experiences from people I know that won‚Äôt go back. The waitress should not be working with the public or get a job she enjoys.
